Description: Automation Works, Inc. specializes in providing computerized systems for the automated control & management of material handling processes.
Full Description: Automation Works, Inc. specializes in providing computerized systems for the automated control and management of material handling processes found in distribution and manufacturing facilities. They refer to these as Process Management Systems. The company has grown from its beginning in 1987 by providing solution tailored specifically to the needs of their customers.  Automation Works integrates equipment from different manufacturers and coordinates the operation of each component using skills in process control, automatic identification, database design and data communications. The core of each system is a data base which stores the information used to control the processes and record operational events, statuses and statistics. Each element of the system accesses the data base and communicates interactively with other elements or with host computer systems using serial communications, local area networks, and wide area networks. The information stored in the data base becomes an integral part of the management of the material handling processes.  They utilize a "building block" approach to system development. A process management system tailored specifically to the customers requirements is built using a set of standard software components, high-level structures and proven techniques. Their experience has shown that each company and its applications are sufficiently different, both in the nature of its business and in the choice of areas to auto that it is generally impractical to distribute "packaged" software. Instead, their emphasis has been on developing tools that allow us to create and customize stable and sophisticated systems, easily and economically.

What differentiates Thar Geothermal from other commercial geothermal systems is the use of an established natural refrigerant, recycled carbon dioxide (known as R744).     Additionally the technology lowers the cost and environmental footprint of system installation which has historically hampered adoption of conventional geothermal technology.  By improving return of investment and lowering market barriers, Thar Geothermal is planning for rapid market penetration.  The company is now in the process of transitioning from a development-stage company to a commercial operating company that designs, builds, installs, and finances sustainable heating and cooling systems.

With offices in Tucson-AZ, Portland-OR and Albuquerque-NM, the company has built a reputation for designing “worry-free” solar-electric systems, as every project comes with a 10-Year Installation Warranty, a 25-Year Panel Performance Warranty with Lifetime Production Monitoring. Because of its long trajectory of building quality solar-electric systems, Stelcor Energy was granted SunPower Dealer status in 2010 – an achievement given only to those integrators that are committed to a higher standard of performance, integrity and customer satisfaction. Stelcor Energy has also built an impressive resume of successfully completed commercial and school solar projects and in the process, developed strategic partnerships with manufacturers, structural steel erectors, and some of the strongest lending institutions in the country.  Our current 2014 commercial-solar backlog consists of 4.1 Megawatts worth of projects totaling $11.3M in revenue. The list includes (3) Arizona charter-school projects currently at final-contract stage and worth $2.2 million (860 kW) and (10) LOI-secured deals worth an additional $9.1 million (3.3 Megawatts). Stelcor Energy's unique and proven ability to enter into new markets by initiating a low-cost, high-energy sales initiative and quickly generating a backlog of projects and revenue, allows for it to enter into targeted market-areas with minimal cost and establish the financial footing required to build a permanent solar-sales presence.

Description: American Bars is a B2B (SAAS) Marketing Platform for Bars that utilizes AI to help bars market with very little interaction.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: American Bars ("AB"), on a high level, is a B2B (SAAS) Marketing Platform for Bars/Pubs (“bars”) that utilizes artificial intelligence and smart database design to help bars market with very little interaction from the bars themselves.   The AB network consists of an extensive web app with bar owner dashboards, bar owner apps, and a consumer app, call BUUZ.  AB uses the historical data of users and bars to recognize patterns and to predict behavior to enhance a user’s experience and to automate bar marketing.    American Bars’ consumer facing app, which is always free to consumers, allows people to find great bars all over the US, along with a lot of other cool functions.  AB tracks a users behavior and use predictive analysis to enhance their app experience, suggest new bars, beer and liquor.  Then, we use their behavioral data to send bars new customers who are predisposed to their type of bar.   Getting consumers to download the app comes directly from bars in large part.  Bars, from either their dashboards or their bar owner app, can upload customer lists or add them individually.  AB is  also integrating with POS systems and using Credit Card data to export customers to the AB system.  Once they do add the customer(s), AB determines whether or not a user has downloaded the AB app.  If they have not, we send a text and a download link asking the user to download the app to follow that specific bar.  When they do download the app, we automatically add that bar as one of their favorites.  If the user already has downloaded the app, AB adds the bar as one of their favorites.  Then, anytime the bar adds an event or has a new special, the customer is notified and it is automatically posted to social media platforms.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Events, Food and Beverage, Media and Entertainment, Travel and Tourism
